div2.p:
"No. I have enough country practice that I need a horse;
                        I'm trying this one. I think of you often so I thought I'd
                        drive out. How are you making it, Kate?"

Any form of religious belief was a subject that never had been touched upon
                        or talked of in the Bates family. Money was their God, work their religion;
                        Kate looked at her mother curiously.

So the families all went to their homes; Kate helped her mother to bed; and
                        then she and Adam, 3d, tried to plan what would be best for the morrow;
                        afterward they sat down and figured until almost dawn.
